quizzes.question:
What is the output of this code?
var arr = new Array(3, 6, 8);
document.write(arr[1]);

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Accessing an Array[/h1]

Attempting to access an index outside of the array, returns the value [b]undefined[/b].[code format="js" codeId="694"]var courses = new Array("HTML", "CSS", "JS"); 
document.write(courses[10]);
//Outputs "[b]undefined[/b]"[/code]
[note]Our [b]courses [/b]array has just 3 elements, so the 10th index, which is the 11th element, does not exist (is undefined).[/note]
